  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed first floor level extension, by reason of&nbsp; excessive bulk, scale, massing and siting would result in an obtrusive and incompatible form of development which would fail to respect the character and appearance of the subject property, terrace of which it forms part and would fail to preserve or enhance the character and appearance of the Clapton Square Conservation Area. As such the proposed development is contrary to policies D3 (Optimising Site Capacity through the Design-led Approach), D4(Delivering good design) and HC1 (Heritage Conservation and Growth) of the London Plan 2021, LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character), LP3 (Designated Heritage Assets) and LP17 (Housing Design) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033, and the guidance contained within Hackney Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD 2009.",
    "The proposed development would result in the provision of substandard accommodation due to lack of outlook and failure to demonstrate the proposed unit would receive sufficient levels of light.&nbsp; As such the proposed development is contrary to policy D6 (Housing Quality and Standards) of London Plan 2021 and&nbsp;Policy&nbsp;LP2 (Development and Amenity) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020).",
    "The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure a contribution towards affordable housing fails to deliver the maximum reasonable amount of affordable housing and is therefore contrary to policy H4 (Delivering affordable housing) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP13 (Affordable housing) of Hackneyâs Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#39;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).",
    "The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure car-free housing, would be likely to promote the use of non-sustainable modes of transport and contribute to air pollution and congestion in the surrounding area, contrary to policies T6 (Car Parking) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP45 (Parking and Car Free Development) of Hackneyâs Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#39;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).",
    "The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to contribute towards the Carbon Offset Fund,&nbsp; would fail to meet the London Objective of being a zero-carbon city by 2050, contrary to policies SI 2 (Minimising greenhouse gas emissions) of the London Plan (2021), policy&nbsp; LP55 (Mitigating Climate Change) of Hackneyâs Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#39;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).",
    "In the absence of a legal agreement to secure a contribution towards a&nbsp; construction management plan monitoring fee, would be likely to result in adverse impacts upon the highways in the surrounding area, contrary to policy LP43 (Transport and development) of Hackneyâs Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#39;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).",
    "The proposed development, by reason of its height, massing, scale and siting would harm the amenity of the neighbouring occupiers within Flats 2 and 3 of 411 Mare Street in respect of loss of outlook to the detriment of their amenity,&amp;nbsp;contrary to Policy&amp;nbsp;D6 (Housing Quality and Standards) of London Plan 2021 and Policy&amp;nbsp;LP2 (Development and Amenity) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020).",
    "The proposed development has failed to demonstrate the current occupiers of Flats 2 and 3 of 411 Mare Street and occupiers No.413 Mare Street would not experience an undue loss of light as a result of the proposed development to the detriment of their amenity, contrary to D6(Housing Quality and Standards) of the London Plan and LP2 (Development and Amenity) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020).",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development has failed to provide cycle parking for the residential use and would therefore fail to promote cycling as a sustainable mode of transport. As such the proposed development is contrary to policies T1 (Strategic Approach to Transport), T4 (Assessing and Mitigating Transport Impacts) and T5 (Cycling) of the London Plan 2021, policies LP42 (Walking and Cycling) and LP43 (Transport and Development) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033(2020) and the guidance contained within Hackney Transport Strategy.&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
